          },
          "datePublished": "2024-05-29",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I have been a student of this school since 2012. This school is the worst school in the world. You cannot expect anything better from this school. You could have expected more if Sir Joseph Matthew was the Director of the School at present but unfortunately Amita Prasad became the new director and under her administration, the school has lost all its beauty. There was a naughty castle which is now removed. Talent is not recognised in this school. There have been many competitions in the school for which we were told to buy things, etc. and the money would be refunded but the money was not refunded. There have been several cases of bone breaking in the past few years. This is my last year in the school and I am glad that I am leaving this bad school and joining South Point. They say that they have got the best students in boards and I also agree that the teachers here are very friendly and good but again, the school has a director and principal. If you don't complete your work on time(they don't consider medical reasons), teachers say to you like a threat that parent call will happen and you will be rusticated. They had many police cases too over the past few years. I request, if you don't want to spoil your children and don't want him/her to suicide due to the pressure put on him/her, please don't admit your child to the school. I hope that this school closes soon as they destroy the future of children. (((Please also note the toilets are bad, the canteen is unhygienic. This school is not a school, instead it is a piece of trash. I even now think about the incident when I bought momos in the canteen(price is very high and is rising everyday by Rs.5), I got food poisoning. The old canteen can be a good place but the new building canteen is the most baddest canteen. We being seniors, never buy anything from the new building canteen.)))",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
