          },
          "datePublished": "2024-02-16",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Absolutely WORST. Don't admit your ward expecting that he or she will learn good values or will become very excellent in academics. This school is completely all about money and politics. The school only knows how to take money from the students and nothing else.\n\nThe school was better when Joseph Mathew was the director, but as I mentioned, the politics existing in this school has thrown him out of the school and the present director only knows money now and just how to promote the school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Indus Valley World School - Ajoy Nagar"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Avishikta Bose"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-01-12",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I was a student here and I got nothing to hide.\nI enjoyed myself here and actually learnt the things needed in life while Joseph Matthew was our Director, it all went downhill from there.\nThe trauma this school put us through is no joke, if I could turn back time then I'd stop myself from entering the school grounds AT ALL COSTS.\nThe building just looks pretty and that's it, if you as a parent think that your child is gonna learn values and gain knowledge here, you're mistaken.\nIf your child is meant to do well in life, they'll do it from any school in Kolkata but if you put them in here, there's no saving your kid anymore.\nEven all the good teachers have left this school, my juniors who are still in school ask me for old notes because the current faculty can't be bothered about the student's future at all and just throw the whole syllabus at them to be covered back home. Why would students even go to school at this point if everything needs to be completed back home as a 'homework'?\nThis school might win awards for its infrastructure and sometimes for sport events but that's it though. There's not much more to it.\nJust don't, its seriously not worth it.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
      ]
